		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2015"></a><br><code>sle2015/paper11</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2015</a> paper:</span><br><i>Supporting efficient and advanced omniscient debugging for xDSMLs</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ErwanBousse.html">Erwan Bousse</a>, <a href="../profile/JonathanCorley.html">Jonathan Corley</a>, <a href="../profile/BenoîtCombemale.html">Benoît Combemale</a>, <a href="../profile/JeffreyGGray.html">Jeffrey G. Gray</a>, <a href="../profile/BenoîtBaudry.html">Benoît Baudry</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2814251.2814262">10.1145/2814251.2814262</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s primary contribution is debugging tooling (omniscient debugging) for executable DSMLs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> Omniscient debugging relies on runtime execution tracing and state navigation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is largely about improving developer interaction with executions (debugging usability).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The target artifacts are executable domain-specific modeling languages (xDSMLs).
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
